There is a QR code on the table in which you use to view the menu.  We ordered the lamb chops with mashed potatoes and stuffed salmon.   It took forever for our food to come out but when it did it was piping hot and delicious.   I was skeptical of order the lamb chops as I feared it wouldn‚Äôt be seasoned or cook well.  Let me tell you I‚Äôm glad I was proven wrong.  The lamb chops were so delicious. As I‚Äôm writing this review, I‚Äôm reminiscing over the taste.  I also tried the lemon cake and ice cream which was also delicious.  The restaurant just needs to improve their wait time.  Give this place a try. It‚Äôs also accessible via public transportation.  I can‚Äôt wait to get back here to taste more entrees.

originalText.text: Very popular brunch spot, ok food but way overpriced. Good fried catfish and chicken, fluffy pancake with blueberry on top. Very very loud and slow service when packed for brunch. Ate at bar and waited forever for menu, drink, order, food and check. Music is very loud so everyone have to shout for convo which makes it even worst. Have great outdoor dance parties during summer.

originalText.text: We had a 12:30 reservation, and waited about ten minutes to be seated. It was crowded and the deejay was setting up. The staff are all very nice. I had the catfish dinner, my sister had the brioche french toast, and my friend had the shrimp and grits. We also ordered the moonshine. My first plate I sent back because the fish was not to my liking, but they immediately brought me out another plate that was  just fine. The food was delicious. I would definitely recommend them for brunch, but if you want to enjoy the deejay come after 2pm. He was jamming as we were leaving üòû

originalText.text: Came here on Saturday around 1pm and it was really busy. Loved the vibes, DJ was a nice touch, and just beautiful black people everywhere‚Äîhow could you not enjoy. However, we sat at the bar and ordered at 12:50 and the food didn‚Äôt come out until 1:50 :/ everyone around us was getting their meals in less time so I‚Äôm not sure what exactly happened. General Manager sent out two baskets of biscuits to make up for it and ultimately gave us a 30% discount. Luckily, the butter with the biscuits and the BLVD wings made up for it. Based off service, I probably would not come again, but worth a try if you have never been.
